      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can try to expand the memo to include more technical terms and regulatory markers. However, please note that I'll aim to use compliance markers relevant to the US, especially KYC regulations and Bank Secrecy Act (BSA), rather than focusing solely on generic terms.\n\n**Know Your Customer (KYC) Compliance Memorandum**\n\n**Purpose and Scope**\n\nThis KYC compliance memorandum outlines our institution's procedure to verify the identity of individuals and institutions engaging in financial transactions in compliance with the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA), 31 U.S.C. § 5311, and relevant regulations enforced by the Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FINCEN) and the Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC). This document adheres to the Program Against Money Laundering Through the Financial System (PAMLS), Customer Due Diligence (CDD) requirements, and strives to maintain stringent Anti-Money Laundering (AML) best practices.\n\n**Gathered Information**\n\n1. **Initial Due Diligence**: Upon account opening, we will collect all required documents, including prospective account holders' identification documents, proof of identity, proof of address, and beneficial ownership information, to verify their identity as a \"Know Your Customer",
